# Cline Rules — VS Code Bootloader

**Read `rules/DIGEST.md` first** — it is the short auto-generated list of
non-negotiables every agent must follow.

**Then read AGENTS.md** — it is the canonical agent entry point and routes you
to the constitution in `rules/` (mandatory: `rules/000-core.md`,
`rules/global.md`, `rules/040-git.md`). Everything below is Cline-specific
routing only; on any conflict, `rules/` wins.

## Model Routing

- TRIVIAL tasks: DeepSeek V3.2 (direct API)
- MODERATE tasks: MiniMax M2.5
- CRITICAL tasks: Claude Sonnet 4.6

## Cost Control

- Maximum 20 requests per task — then stop and report
- If a task exceeds $2 in cost → STOP and announce it
- Keep the system prompt stable (higher cache-hit rate)

## Behavior

- Read the `memory-bank/` files before every task
- Read the rule files from `.agent/rules/`
- Read any file before editing it
- Never delete a file without approval
- Never write secrets into code

## After Every Task

- Update `memory-bank/activeContext.md`
- Run `ruff` + `pytest`
- Summarize the result in one line

## Source of Truth (2026-07-01)

- **Tasks:** `~/.local/share/agent-projects/_memory/TODO.md` — read section
  `## <project>` (repo name, lowercased) + `## 🌐 Cross-project`. Never a
  per-repo `TODO.md`.
- **Personal data** (keys, CVs, `SESSION.md`): vault
  `~/.local/share/agent-projects/<project>/`, never the repo. Shared LLM keys:
  `_shared/secrets/.env`.
- **Git:** branch first; no AI attribution in commits (rule `040-git`); get
  approval before merge.
